[b]Reversal Engine Score v1[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Reversal Engine Score fires a signal only when a liquidity sweep is confirmed by HTF trend alignment and enough scoring conditions are met. Each bar earns points across ten conditions — the signal fires only when the total reaches your chosen minimum. This keeps the signal count low and evidence-backed.

[b]How signals form[/b]
[list]
[*]A [b]liquidity sweep[/b] occurs: price violates a prior swing high/low and recovers by close on the same bar
[*]The [b]HTF trend filter[/b] confirms direction (fast EMA vs. slow EMA on your chosen HTF)
[*]The [b]score gate[/b] is met — default minimum is 7 out of a possible 12 points
[*]No signal is in [b]cooldown[/b] from a recent entry
[/list]

[b]Score breakdown (max 12 pts)[/b]
[list]
[*][b]HTF trend aligned[/b] — 2 pts
[*][b]Liquidity sweep with recovery close[/b] — 2 pts
[*][b]EMA + RSI momentum in signal direction[/b] — 1 pt
[*][b]Close in upper / lower third of candle range[/b] — 1 pt
[*][b]ATR above baseline × factor[/b] — 1 pt
[*][b]Candle body above ATR × factor[/b] — 1 pt
[*][b]EMA slope in signal direction[/b] — 1 pt
[*][b]RSI rising / falling[/b] — 1 pt
[*][b]Close breaks prior bar high / low[/b] — 1 pt
[*][b]Bull / bear candle[/b] — 1 pt
[/list]

[b]Tuning[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Default (7 pts, cooldown 5)[/b] — balanced; moderate signal frequency
[*][b]Strict (8–9 pts, cooldown 8–12, TP 2.5 ATR)[/b] — fewer, higher-conviction signals
[*][b]15M-only mode[/b] — orange background on other timeframes to avoid accidental use
[/list]

[b]Outputs[/b]
[list]
[*]BUY / SELL shape markers with score label
[*]ATR-based SL and TP lines plotted at the signal bar
[*]HTF trend background (optional)
[*]Hidden plots for strategy use: entry, stop, take, direction, score
[*]Alert conditions for BUY, SELL, and either
[/list]

